Optimized Code (C++)

class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* addTwoNumbers(ListNode* l1, ListNode* l2) {
        ListNode* dummy = new ListNode(0);
        ListNode* temp = dummy;

        int carry = 0;

        while(l1 != NULL || l2 != NULL || carry){

            int sum = carry;

            if(l1){
                sum += l1->val;
                l1 = l1->next;
            }

            if(l2){
                sum += l2->val;
                l2 = l2->next;
            }

            temp->next = new ListNode(sum % 10);

            carry = sum / 10;

            temp = temp->next;
        }

        return dummy->next;
    }
};
Interview Explanation
Step 1

"I create a dummy node to store the answer."

Step 2

"I traverse both linked lists together."

Step 3

"For every node, I add the first digit, second digit, and carry."

Step 4

"The new node stores sum % 10, and the new carry is sum / 10."

Step 5

"I continue until both linked lists and the carry are finished."


